      "content": "Your orchestrator is cec50b17:0. Work inside `.synapse/worktrees/developer-25-shorten-read-messages-desc`. Commit your changes. Do not push.\n\nIn `src/mcp-server.ts`, find the `read_messages` tool description (around line 91). It currently reads:\n\n```typescript\n`Check for instructions from the human operator. Your agent ID is \"${AGENT_ID}\". ` +\n'Call this at the START of every turn before doing anything else. ' +\n'Returns unread messages addressed to you, ordered by priority (0 = urgent). ' +\n'When there are messages, the first content block is a JSON array where each element has: ' +\n'{ id: number, from: string, priority: 0|5, at: string (ISO timestamp), content: string }. ' +\n'Use the `id` field as `source_msg_id` when calling `delegate_task`.',\n```\n\nReplace it with this shorter version:\n\n```typescript\n`Check for instructions from the human operator. Your agent ID is \"${AGENT_ID}\". ` +\n'Returns unread messages as a JSON array: { id, from, priority, at, content }. ' +\n'Use the id field as source_msg_id when calling delegate_task.',\n```\n\nThe \"Call this at the START of every turn\" line is removed because Rule 1 in SYNAPSE.md already covers it. The return format is kept (needed for parsing). Build with `npm run build` and verify clean.",
